query:
CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS `pirPrograms` (
  `id` int AUTO_INCREMENT PRIMARY KEY,
  `name` varchar(255) NOT NULL,
  `description` text,
  `startDate` date NOT NULL,
  `endDate` date,
  `status` enum('active', 'inactive', 'completed') NOT NULL DEFAULT 'active',
  `coordinatorId` int,
  `coordinatorName` varchar(255),
  `requiresMedicalExam` boolean NOT NULL DEFAULT true,
  `requiresTraining` boolean NOT NULL DEFAULT true,
  `testFrequencyMonths` int NOT NULL DEFAULT 12,
  `createdBy` int,
  `createdByName` varchar(255),
  `createdAt` timestamp NOT NULL DEFAULT CURRENT_TIMESTAMP,
  `updatedAt` timestamp NOT NULL DEFAULT CURRENT_TIMESTAMP ON UPDATE CURRENT_TIMESTAMP
)
